OL,3,CWorld Bee Day: Celebrating the all-
OL,4,Cimportant pollinators
OL,6,F'World Bee Day' is celebrated on 20
OL,7,FMay each year, and aims to acknowledge
OL,8,Fthe role that bees - and other
OL,9,Fpollinators - play in our ecosystem.
OL,11,FOne third of the UK bee population has
OL,12,Fdeclined in the last 10 years. The
OL,13,Fmain causes are loss of habitat for
OL,14,Fnesting and foraging, climate change
OL,15,Fand the use of chemical pesticides.
OL,17,FThe easiest way we can help our bees
OL,18,Fthrive is by planting bee friendly,
OL,19,Fnative plants in our gardens that
OL,20,Fflower at different times of the year.
