OL,3,CWorld Bee Day: Celebrating the all-
OL,4,Cimportant pollinators
OL,6,FOnly female bees can sting. Male bees
OL,7,Fdon't have the anatomy to do so. And -
OL,8,Funlike the more aggressive relation,
OL,9,Fthe wasp (yellow jacket) - bees rarely
OL,10,Fsting...only when they feel
OL,11,Fthreatened. It is only the honey bee
OL,12,Fthat will die after stinging, not the
OL,13,Fbumble bee!
OL,15,FThey're Speedy!
OL,17,FWorker bees can reach a speed of 15-20
OL,18,Fmph when flying to a food source, and
OL,19,Fabout 12 mph when returning laden down
OL,20,Fwith nectar, pollen, propolis or water.
